  "notes": {
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/roman-to-integer?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "When scanning from right to left, you've already seen the symbol to the right\n- If the current value is smaller than the previous value, it must be part of a subtractive pair (like IV, IX, XL), so subtract it.\n- Otherwise, add it.",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-duplicates-from-sorted-array?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "You need to copy the first occurrence of each distinct value, not the last one",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/next-permutation?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "The key is to make the smallest possible increase to the current permutation.\n- Find the dip\n- Swap with next greater from right\n- Reverse the suffix.",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/trapping-rain-water?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "Smaller max decides. Update max → collect water → move pointer.",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/powx-n?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "- x always stores the current power of 2 (x¹, x², x⁴, x⁸, ...).\n- Odd (n % 2 == 1) means \"take this power\", so do ans *= x.\n- Then square x (next power) and halve n (move to the next binary bit).",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/sort-colors?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "Use mid to track current element\n- Swap with l (0) → incoming element is already processed (1) → ✅ mid++\n- Swap with r (2) → incoming element is unknown → ❌ don't mid++",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-consecutive-sequence?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "Only start from numbers with no predecessor (num - 1 absent)\n- Keep moving forward while num + 1 exists",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/lru-cache?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "Map finds, DLL orders. Every access goes to MRU. Evict from LRU.\n- Access → Move Right\n- Overflow → Remove Left\n\nHashMap → Find any node in O(1)\nDLL → Maintain usage order in O(1)\n\nLRU <-> ... <-> ... <-> MRU\n ^\nleft                    right",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/reverse-linked-list?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "During the iterative reversal, the list is temporarily split into two parts\n- The already reversed part\n- The remaining unreversed part\n\nThe curr pointer is always the boundary between them",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/subarray-sum-equals-k?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "A subarray is a contiguous non-empty sequence of elements within an array\n\nStore all previous prefix sums. At each position\n- What previous prefix would make the current subarray satisfy the condition?\n- Then add the current prefix to the map\n\n- Prefix Sum + HashMap pattern",
    "https://leetcode.com/problems/spiral-matrix?envType=company&amp;envId=google&amp;favoriteSlug=google-three-months": "Walk the perimeter, then shrink the perimeter\n\nTreat the matrix as shrinking rectangles.\nAfter traversing one edge, move that boundary inward.\n\nRepeat while a rectangle still exists:\n\n- Traverse left → right on top\ntop += 1\n- Traverse top → bottom on right\nright -= 1\n- Traverse right → left on bottom\nbottom -= 1\n- Traverse bottom → top on left\nleft += 1",
